President Trump made remarks before departing to Normandy, expressing his anticipation for a special and important day. He mentioned the ongoing discussions with Mexico and the need for progress on immigration issues. He criticized Congress, particularly the Democrats, for their lack of action on immigration laws and accused them of wanting free immigration into the country. He stated that solving the immigration problem would be easy if the Democrats were willing to make changes. He also discussed the ongoing talks with China and the potential for a deal. President Trump emphasized the effectiveness of tariffs and stated that the United States is the "piggybank" that others want to take from, but they are not taking it as easily anymore. He concluded by expressing his satisfaction with the tariffs on China and his determination to do what is necessary at the right time.